contentrichtext.text: '''Yeleninskoye''' ({{lang-ru|Еле́нинское}}) was a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|village]] in [[Agapovsky District]] of [[Chelyabinsk Oblast]], [[Russia]].<ref Name="Shimkin">{{cite book |title=Minerals |last=Shimkin |first=Demitri Boris |authorlink=Demitri Boris Shimkin |coauthors= |year=1953 |publisher=Harvard University Press |location= |isbn= |page=229 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=Rd8wAAAAIAAJ&q=Yeleninskoye&dq=Yeleninskoye&client=firefox-a&pgis=1}}</ref> It is the birthplace of [[Vasily Zaytsev]], a famous [[World War II]] [[Soviet sniper]]. ==References== {{Reflist}} {{coord|53.1222|N|59.8819|E|source:kolossus-nlwiki|display=title}} [[Category:Rural localities in Chelyabinsk Oblast]] {{ChelyabinskOblast-geo-stub}}
